    </Ingredient>
  </Ingredients>
  <Method>
    <Step image="">Heat olive oil in a large, heavy, lidded sauce pan.</Step>
    <Step image="">Cook carrots and onions until translucent but not caramelized.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add garlic and continue to sauté until you can smell the garlic.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add tomato concassé, paste, oregano, bay leaves and red pepper flakes.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add just enough water to thin the mixture in preparation for simmering.  Simmer, covered, until the sauce reaches the desired thickness and consistency.</Step>
    <Step image="">Taste and add salt to adjust the seasoning.  Depending on the type and quality of your tomatoes, the sauce may be either too sour or not sour enough for your taste.  Add vinegar to increase tartness.  Add sweet vermouth to reduce the tartness.</Step>
    <Step image="">Finish the sauce by adding the basil and parsley. </Step>
  </Method>
  <Variations/>
</Recipe>